CAPE Town City striker Kermit Erasmus has joined Mamelodi Sundowns, the club have confirmed. The 30-year-old had been on the radar of the Brazilians for quite some time with Downs desperate for his services. The Tshwane giants, as they often do, have finally got their man. "Cape Town City and Mamelodi Sundowns have reached an agreement over the transfer of Kermit Erasmus," the Citizens wrote on social media. "A hero in the City shirt, we wish him the best of luck in the next phase of his career!" Erasmus, who is coming from one of his best seasons in the PSL last term, will hope to reproduce it in the colours of Sundowns. He is expected to join his new side after the international break. 